				<td colspan="2"><span>If you add an Augment to an item that modifies a skill,
<br />
it is a skill modifier and Not an Instrument.
<br />

<br />
If you add a Wind Instr. Modifier to a ring it is a ring,
<br />
not a flute.
<br />

<br />
I can see where this causes confusion, what with some
<br />
Planes of Power items/armor doubling as instruments.
<br />

<br />
IMHO what they were getting at with the augmentations
<br />
that assist bardic skills was to offer a way to gain/retian
<br />
a skill modifier without having to wield the
<br />
Singing Short Sword. (I have better, but use the epic...)
<br />
Of course the drawback is what you are experiencing -
<br />
ie. not being able to sing Invis (flute) or OOS (drum). =(
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Or I'm wrong and it is supposed to *become* an instrument
<br />
via the augmentation, then yeah, it's busted.
<br />
(But I still think it is a modifier, not an instrument.)</span></td>
